On beginning one of those constantly-vowed journals.
December 28th, 2012. I am 23, on an airplane to Charlotte SC to attend something called a renaissance weekend. Martin Gardener will be there, which I suppose is exciting.

I want to work at an edutech startup. I want to make Neal Stephenson a prophet. I want to make Sal Khan a Nobel Peace Prize winner. I want to make myself a Young Professional (tm). My punk-as-fuck (which I think is actually the technical term) haircut undercuts this desire.

I have recently developed a profound feat of flying, combattable with Valium, which I have taken on about half of my flights since it was perscribed. I find turbulence comforting. Nothing bad will happen from turbulence. I